<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-22T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-22T05:00:00-05:00" n="23" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 General Committee/797:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The American Delegate</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-22T11:00:00+01:00">February 22, 1934—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 22—7:38 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>819. Your 403, February 20, 5 p.m.<note n="65" xml:id="d23fn65">Not
                                    printed; it contained text of American memorandum of February
                                    19, 1934, to the British Embassy, <ref target="#pg_22">p.
                                        22</ref>.</note> I venture to suggest that the German
                                    Ambassador<note n="66" xml:id="d23fn66">Hans Luther.</note>
                                should also be apprised. Not only is Germany an active party to this
                                four power discussion but its attitude on reduction may in the long
                                run be decisive.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>